view.name: Changes in Net Position
view.description:
CAFR Pages 332-335.

Net Position is the difference between the Cityâ€™s assets and liabilities, including deferred outflows/inflows of resources. This data summarizes the change in Net Position by Change Types, Asset Types, and Activities. This data is based on the following parameters: Accrual Basis of Accounting, Last Ten Fiscal Years and (amounts expressed in thousands).

columns.name: Fiscal Year
columns.description: Fiscal Year (FY) is the time period for the City budget which begins on July 1 of a calendar year and ends on June 30 of the following year.

columns.name: Change Type
columns.description: Type of outflows/inflows to the Net Position (Assets minus Liabilities)

top.item: General Revenues and Other Changes in Net Position

columns.name: Activity Type
columns.description: Governmental Activities are functions principally supported by taxes and intergovernmental revenues. Business-Type Activities are functions intended to recover all (or in large part) costs through user fees and charges. Special Items are those that are not Governmental or Business-type Activities.

top.item: Transfer of Housing Loans from CRA

columns.name: Amount in Thousands
columns.description: Changes in Net Position (Assets minus Liabilities) in Thousands of Dollars

columns.name: Absolute Amount in Thousands
columns.description: Absolute Value of changes in Net Position (Assets minus Liabilities) in Thousands of Dollars
